---
import ContentApp from '../../layouts/ContentApp.astro'
---

<ContentApp
  title="About"
  description="PAI is a bootable live-USB OS that gives you a private, offline AI workstation you can carry anywhere — Debian 12, Sway, Ollama, no telemetry."
>
  <nav slot="sidebar">
    <p class="sb-brand">About</p>
    <a href="#what-pai-is" class="sb-link">What PAI is</a>
    <a href="#what-you-get" class="sb-link">What you get</a>
    <a href="#who-its-for" class="sb-link">Who it's for</a>
    <a href="#what-its-not" class="sb-link">What it's not</a>
    <hr class="sb-divider" />
    <a
      href="https://github.com/nirholas/pai"
      class="sb-link"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      style="font-size:0.8125rem"
    >
      View on GitHub ↗
    </a>
    <a href="/apps/how-it-works" class="sb-link" style="font-size:0.8125rem">How PAI works →</a>
    <a href="/apps/docs" class="sb-link" style="font-size:0.8125rem">Documentation →</a>
    <a href="/apps/faq" class="sb-link" style="font-size:0.8125rem">FAQ →</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>PAI</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">
      Private AI on a bootable USB drive.<br />
      Your secure, offline-first AI assistant — carry it anywhere, leave no trace.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-screenshot" aria-label="PAI desktop preview">
      <div
        class="hero-mock"
        role="img"
        aria-label="PAI desktop — windows, dock, and topbar"
      >
        <div class="hero-mock-topbar">
          <span class="hero-mock-topbar-item hero-mock-topbar-brand">PAI</span>
          <span class="hero-mock-topbar-item">Workspace 1</span>
          <span class="hero-mock-topbar-spacer"></span>
          <span class="hero-mock-topbar-item">12:34</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-mock-stage">
          <div class="hero-mock-window hero-mock-window--a">
            <div class="hero-mock-window-chrome">
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-mock-window-body">
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:80%"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:60%"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:72%"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:45%"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-mock-window hero-mock-window--b">
            <div class="hero-mock-window-chrome">
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-dot"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-mock-window-body">
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:55%"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:78%"></span>
              <span class="hero-mock-line" style="width:40%"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-mock-dock">
          <span class="hero-mock-dock-item"></span>
          <span class="hero-mock-dock-item"></span>
          <span class="hero-mock-dock-item"></span>
          <span class="hero-mock-dock-item"></span>
          <span class="hero-mock-dock-item"></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-screenshot-caption">PAI desktop (Sway + Waybar + PAI UI)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-row">
      <button class="btn btn--primary" data-open-app="Flash">Download PAI</button>
      <button class="btn" data-open-app="Verify">Verify ISO</button>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/nirholas/pai"
        class="btn"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        View on GitHub ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What PAI is -->
  <section id="what-pai-is">
    <h2>What PAI is</h2>
    <p>
      PAI is a <strong>bootable live USB operating system</strong> built on Debian 12
      that gives you a private, portable AI workstation. Plug it into any x86-64 PC, boot from USB,
      and you have a complete AI environment that leaves no trace behind.
    </p>
    <p>
      Like <a href="https://tails.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tails</a> is to
      privacy-focused browsing, PAI is to <strong>private AI</strong>. It combines the amnesic,
      leave-no-trace philosophy of Tails with the power of local large language models running via{' '}
      <a href="https://ollama.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ollama</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Your conversations exist only in RAM while PAI is running. Shut down, and they're gone — no
      logs, no history, no server-side copies. The machine doesn't even know PAI was there.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- What you get -->
  <section id="what-you-get">
    <h2>What you get</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">🤖</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Offline AI assistant</strong> — Ollama runs Llama, Mistral, Phi, Gemma, and 100+
          models locally. No API keys, no cloud, no data leaving your machine.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">🔒</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Privacy-hardened environment</strong> — MAC spoofing on every boot, UFW firewall
          denying all inbound connections, optional Tor routing.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">🖥️</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Complete desktop</strong> — Sway (Wayland tiling WM), Firefox ESR, terminal (foot),
          file manager, text editor. Everything you need, nothing you don't.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">💾</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Zero installation</strong> — boots entirely from USB into RAM. Nothing touches the
          host machine's hard drive.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">🔑</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Crypto wallets</strong> — Electrum (Bitcoin) and Monero wallet pre-configured with
          sane privacy defaults.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fi" aria-hidden="true">🛡️</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Encrypted persistence (opt-in)</strong> — save AI models, SSH keys, and chat
          history to a LUKS2-encrypted partition on the USB across sessions.
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Who it's for -->
  <section id="who-its-for">
    <h2>Who it's for</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Privacy-conscious users</strong> who want to use AI without sending prompts to
        corporate servers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Journalists and researchers</strong> who work with sensitive sources and documents.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Security professionals</strong> who need an isolated, trusted environment for
        sensitive analysis.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Crypto users</strong> who want to manage wallets on a network-isolated machine.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Travelers</strong> who want to use AI on any computer without leaving traces.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Developers</strong> who want to experiment with local LLMs without cloud
        dependencies or costs.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- What it's not -->
  <section id="what-its-not">
    <h2>What it's not</h2>
    <p>PAI raises the cost of surveillance significantly, but informed expectations matter:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Not a GPU rig</strong> — CPU-only inference. Expect 5–20 tokens/sec for 7B models.
        Fast enough for most tasks; use smaller models for speed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Not Tails</strong> — Tails routes everything through Tor by default. PAI makes Tor
        opt-in. PAI's focus is private AI, not anonymous browsing — though you can combine both.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Not a permanent install</strong> — PAI is a live system. It boots from USB. No
        traditional hard drive installation.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Not protection against physical attacks</strong> — hardware keyloggers, compromised
        BIOS/UEFI firmware, and cold boot attacks are out of scope.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Not cloud AI</strong> — you get what runs on your hardware. Local models are
        powerful and improving rapidly, but they're not GPT-4.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTAs -->
  <div class="cta-row cta-row--bottom">
    <button class="btn btn--primary" data-open-app="Flash">Download PAI</button>
    <button class="btn" data-open-app="Verify">Verify ISO</button>
    <a href="https://github.com/nirholas/pai" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >View on GitHub ↗</a
    >
  </div>
</ContentApp>

<style>
  .hero {
    margin-bottom: var(--s-8);
  }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-5);
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .hero-screenshot {
    border-radius: var(--r-window);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
    overflow: hidden;
    gap: var(--s-3);
  }

  .hero-mock {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: #0f0f1a;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .hero-mock-topbar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--s-3);
    padding: 6px 10px;
    background: #181826;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
  }

  .hero-mock-topbar-spacer {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .hero-mock-topbar-brand {
    color: var(--pai-blue);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hero-mock-stage {
    flex: 1;
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--s-4);
  }

  .hero-mock-window {
    position: absolute;
    background: #1c1c2a;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .hero-mock-window--a {
    top: 10%;
    left: 6%;
    width: 52%;
    height: 70%;
  }

  .hero-mock-window--b {
    top: 28%;
    right: 6%;
    width: 46%;
    height: 60%;
  }

  .hero-mock-window-chrome {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    background: #232333;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero-mock-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #3a3a4d;
  }

  .hero-mock-window-body {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 10px;
  }

  .hero-mock-line {
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: #2a2a3d;
  }

  .hero-mock-dock {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 6px;
    background: #181826;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero-mock-dock-item {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: #2a2a3d;
  }

  .hero-screenshot-caption {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--s-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .cta-row--bottom {
    margin-top: var(--s-7);
    padding-top: var(--s-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .btn {
    padding: 7px var(--s-5);
    border-radius: var(--r-icon);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    color: var(--fg);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      background 0.1s,
      color 0.1s,
      border-color 0.1s;
    display: inline-block;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--border);
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .btn--primary {
    background: var(--pai-blue);
    color: #0f0f1a;
    border-color: transparent;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .btn--primary:hover {
    background: var(--pai-yellow);
    border-color: transparent;
    color: #0f0f1a;
  }

  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-5);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-3);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--s-3);
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .fi {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    width: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
